 And she was grateful for the support of her friend Max, whose music had helped her find her own voice as an artist.',6),(114,34,'Once upon a time, in a small town during colonial times, there lived a boy named Jacob. Jacob was thirteen years old and he loved to explore the woods and learn about the history of his town. He often visited the local museum where the curator, Ms. Jenkins, would tell him stories about the people who lived in the town long ago.',0),(115,34,'One day, while Jacob was exploring the woods, he stumbled upon an old map buried under a pile of leaves. Excitedly, he dusted off the map and noticed that it was a treasure map from the colonial times! Jacob knew that he had to find out more about this map, so he decided to visit Ms. Jenkins at the museum.',1),(116,34,'Ms. Jenkins was thrilled to see the old treasure map and told Jacob that it belonged to Captain William, a famous pirate who used to roam the seas near their town. She explained that Captain William had hidden his treasure somewhere in the woods before he was captured by the king\'s men and sent to jail.',2),(117,34,'Eager to find the treasure, Jacob asked Ms. Jenkins if she would help him decode the map. Together, they studied the map and tried to match it with the current landmarks in the woods. After a few hours of deciphering the old map, they finally discovered a secret cave marked on the map.',3),(118,34,'Excited to explore the cave, Jacob and Ms. Jenkins waited until the next morning to begin their adventure. As they ventured into the woods, they followed the map and eventually came across the hidden cave. With a sense of curiosity and anticipation, they entered the cave, eager to find the long-lost treasure of Captain William.',4),(119,34,'Inside the cave, they found an old chest covered in dust and cobwebs. With trembling hands, Jacob opened the chest and was amazed to find it filled with gold coins, jewels, and other treasures. Ms. Jenkins explained that Captain William had hidden his treasure to keep it safe from the king\'s men, and now it had been discovered after all those years.',5),(120,34,'Overwhelmed with joy, Jacob and Ms. Jenkins decided to donate the treasure to the local museum so that everyone could learn about the town\'s history and the adventures of Captain William. The townspeople were amazed by the discovery and marveled at the treasures from colonial times.',6),(121,34,'From that day on, Jacob became known as the brave young explorer who had uncovered the long-lost treasure of Captain William. He continued to visit the museum, eager to learn more about the history of his town and the people who had lived there before him. And every time he looked at the treasure map, he was reminded of the exciting adventure that had brought the town\'s history to life.',7),(122,35,'Once upon a time, in a beautiful garden, there were many animals and bugs. There were butterflies fluttering from flower to flower, bees buzzing around collecting nectar, and birds chirping happily in the trees. There were also some fluffy cats playing and napping in the sun.',0),(123,35,'One sunny day, a little girl named Lily visited the garden with her pet cat, Whiskers. Whiskers was a mischievous orange tabby cat that loved to explore. As soon as Lily let him off the leash, Whiskers darted off to chase butterflies and climb trees.',1),(124,35,'Lily loved watching Whiskers play, but she also wanted to explore the garden. She started to chase after her cat, giggling as she ran. Suddenly, Whiskers stopped and crouched low to the ground, his tail swishing back and forth. Lily looked closer and saw that Whiskers had found a ladybug! It was crawling slowly on a leaf, its red shell dotted with black spots.',2),(125,35,'Lily and Whiskers watched the ladybug for a while, and then they continued their adventure through the garden. They saw bees buzzing around the flowers, collecting pollen, and birds singing in the trees. Whiskers even tried to pounce on a butterfly, but it flew away just in time!',3),(126,35,'As the sun started to set, Lily and Whiskers headed home, tired but happy from their day of exploring. They both fell asleep, dreaming of the wonderful animals and bugs they had seen in the garden. And when they woke up the next morning, they knew they would visit the garden again soon to see all their friends.',4),(127,36,'Madhav and Haley met in the most unexpected way during Madhav\'s college graduation trip to the United States. Haley, a blonde girl with a radiant smile, caught Madhav\'s attention at a local coffee shop. What started as a polite conversation about their favorite coffee turned into a deep connection that neither of them expected. Despite coming from different cultural backgrounds, they found an instant connection that transcended their differences.',0),(128,36,'As they spent more time together, Madhav and Haley learned to appreciate each other\'s unique perspectives and traditions. Madhav shared stories of his upbringing in India, while Haley introduced him to her American way of life. They laughed about their cultural differences and found joy in learning from each other. Their love story blossomed against all odds, proving that love knows no boundaries.',1),(129,36,'Haley was still in college, pursuing her degree in art, while Madhav had just graduated and was looking for job opportunities in his hometown. The geographical distance between them posed a challenge, but they were both determined to make their relationship work. They stayed in touch through video calls, messages, and letters, making an effort to bridge the gap between them.',2),(130,36,'Madhav\'s family welcomed Haley with open arms when she visited India, and Haley\'s family embraced Madhav with warmth and kindness when he visited the United States. Despite the cultural contrasts, both families recognized the love and happiness that Madhav and Haley brought to each other\'s lives. Their support and acceptance strengthened Madhav and 